1
00:01:29,620 --> 00:01:33,150
[Cage of Shadows]

2
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:36,150
[Episode 17]

3
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:15,960
I told you before—
whoever loses the competition

4
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:18,120
will be punished.

5
00:02:24,660 --> 00:02:27,740
I'll give you one night
to think it over.

6
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:29,320
By dawn,

7
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:31,440
I expect to see a corpse.

8
00:02:31,460 --> 00:02:33,460
And if there isn't one

9
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:36,030
by tomorrow morning?

10
00:02:37,079 --> 00:02:38,130
Then I'll have

11
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:40,190
to collect all your bodies.

12
00:03:52,210 --> 00:03:53,329
So

13
00:03:54,230 --> 00:03:56,079
you're not as fragile as you look.

14
00:03:56,079 --> 00:03:57,280
I don't have a choice.

15
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:58,840
I need to survive.

16
00:03:59,610 --> 00:04:01,150
They sent you to kill me?

17
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:04,610
I'm nothing
more than a female prisoner.

18
00:04:04,610 --> 00:04:06,290
I never did anything.

19
00:04:06,650 --> 00:04:07,360
But

20
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,240
ever since you arrived,

21
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:10,970
this place has become strange.

22
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:14,290
I've never seen the present
target anyone like this before.

23
00:04:14,290 --> 00:04:15,440
Who exactly are you?

24
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:18,290
Instead of asking me,

25
00:04:19,060 --> 00:04:21,589
maybe you should
ask yourself that question.

26
00:04:21,620 --> 00:04:22,550
What do you mean?

27
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:25,850
You should know these tricks well enough.

28
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:27,520
After all,

29
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:31,840
you used to be one of them,

30
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:33,600
didn't you?

31
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:38,080
Voice-Keeper Taiyin.

32
00:04:44,310 --> 00:04:45,490
What are you talking about?

33
00:04:45,490 --> 00:04:46,620
I don't understand.

34
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:51,380
How fitting.

35
00:04:51,650 --> 00:04:53,150
Do you remember

36
00:04:53,520 --> 00:04:54,600
this guiding ring?

37
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:57,060
It isn't mine.

38
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:04,400
Who are you?

39
00:05:04,580 --> 00:05:05,640
Who are you really?

40
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:07,310
Where did you get that ring?

41
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:12,640
Do you still remember Nan Shiren's family

42
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:15,610
at the foot of Guitian Mountain
outside the capital?

43
00:05:17,730 --> 00:05:18,850
Nan Shiren...

44
00:05:18,870 --> 00:05:21,840
He once had a simple,
happy family of three.

45
00:05:21,980 --> 00:05:23,270
But one day,

46
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:25,630
an assassin broke in

47
00:05:25,940 --> 00:05:27,800
and killed him in a single strike.

48
00:05:28,740 --> 00:05:31,340
His wife was also poisoned
with a deadly toxin,

49
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:34,480
and to this day,
she's still bedridden.

50
00:05:37,540 --> 00:05:38,940
I already told you,

51
00:05:39,320 --> 00:05:40,260
I'm not...

52
00:06:01,090 --> 00:06:03,800
What kind of skill is it
to bully a child?

53
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:06,500
A child?

54
00:06:07,530 --> 00:06:09,480
I thought so too at first.

55
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:12,160
But I've been observing you
these past few days,

56
00:06:12,300 --> 00:06:14,890
and I've realized—
you're not a child at all.

57
00:06:14,910 --> 00:06:16,830
Your appearance can deceive people,

58
00:06:16,830 --> 00:06:19,250
but your real skin

59
00:06:20,460 --> 00:06:21,900
tells the truth.

60
00:06:29,180 --> 00:06:31,910
As expected—
fine on the outside, rotten within.

61
00:06:32,670 --> 00:06:34,600
Your body has already decayed,

62
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:35,990
just like your heart.

63
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:37,290
So,

64
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:38,909
still going to deny it?

65
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,560
Could it be…

66
00:06:41,570 --> 00:06:42,370
you are…

67
00:06:44,010 --> 00:06:45,010
I am.

68
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:47,920
I am!

69
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:49,040
Tell me—

70
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:51,159
why did you kill my father? Why?

71
00:06:51,180 --> 00:06:52,800
He had already retired into the mountains,
living in seclusion.

72
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,350
He stayed out of all worldly affairs.

73
00:06:54,350 --> 00:06:56,360
Why did you have to hunt him down
and kill him?

74
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,960
Why?

75
00:06:59,440 --> 00:07:01,050
I have the antidote.

76
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:03,250
If I die,

77
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:04,200
your mother…

78
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:06,250
your mother will die too.

79
00:07:19,050 --> 00:07:20,280
The Tower Master

80
00:07:20,370 --> 00:07:22,300
has been overworked again lately—

81
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,630
you've even gotten more gray hairs.

82
00:07:24,630 --> 00:07:25,460
Well,

83
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,600
can I not be overworked?

84
00:07:28,490 --> 00:07:30,410
If I don't worry more,

85
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:33,480
Zhuang Wujiu will tear
the whole place down.

86
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,600
Please calm down, Tower Master.

87
00:07:36,820 --> 00:07:39,020
Wujiu is just young.

88
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:41,080
Once she's been through more,

89
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:43,580
she'll come to understand your intentions.

90
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:59,040
There's still something

91
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:01,400
I can't quite put my mind
at ease about.

92
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:03,600
Tower Master, please give your orders.

93
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:14,020
I'm worried Wujiu won't be able
to bring herself to do it.

94
00:08:14,020 --> 00:08:15,750
If she can't go through with it…

95
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:18,120
you'll need to help her.

96
00:08:20,890 --> 00:08:23,040
The poison your mother was given

97
00:08:23,110 --> 00:08:24,770
was personally crafted by me.

98
00:08:25,940 --> 00:08:27,730
Any standard antidote

99
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:30,030
requires my blood—

100
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:31,600
without it,

101
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:34,470
no one can cure her.

102
00:09:00,560 --> 00:09:02,290
So you really can't be trusted.

103
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:04,570
The antidote is real.

104
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,570
But you must die tonight—

105
00:09:06,590 --> 00:09:09,190
otherwise I won't live
to see tomorrow either.

106
00:09:31,990 --> 00:09:32,990
Master!

107
00:09:38,260 --> 00:09:38,940
Master!

108
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:40,120
The antidote!

109
00:09:40,160 --> 00:09:41,280
I found the antidote!

110
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:42,520
My mother can be saved!

111
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,430
Wujiu,

112
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,280
why did you put your blade away?

113
00:09:45,490 --> 00:09:46,490
Keep going.

114
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:48,600
I was sent by the Tower Master

115
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:50,040
to keep an eye on you—

116
00:09:50,060 --> 00:09:52,140
don't disappoint him.

117
00:09:52,170 --> 00:09:53,010
Shut up!

118
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:59,200
Do you still

119
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:01,750
not know Zhuang Wujiu's real identity?

120
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:02,740
Wan Hongliu,

121
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:04,240
I told you to shut up!

122
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:11,880
Nan Yanzhi,

123
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:14,020
the Tower Master of Lingya Tower…

124
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:16,750
is my father.

125
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:26,640
Master…

126
00:10:26,810 --> 00:10:28,270
you're lying to me, right?

127
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:30,110
You must be lying to me…

128
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:35,120
How foolish.

129
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:37,160
A little kindness

130
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:38,820
and you believed everything.

131
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:41,160
Back then, the order to wipe
out your entire family—

132
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:42,120
that was given

133
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:45,000
by me to Qi Songyue.

134
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:46,410
Impossible…

135
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:48,000
impossible…

136
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,160
how could that be?

137
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:55,960
We were the ones who saved you back then!

138
00:10:56,170 --> 00:10:57,680
I treated you like my own family—

139
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:58,730
how could you?

140
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:01,760
Then why didn't you kill me back then?

141
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:07,880
Because watching you suffer

142
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:09,180
and break apart

143
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:11,920
is far more interesting.

144
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:13,900
I taught you, didn't I?

145
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:16,560
Never trust anyone.

146
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,440
Master,

147
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:21,200
tell me it's all a lie.

148
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:22,600
You raised me,

149
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:24,650
taught me martial arts,

150
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:26,520
and took care of my family.

151
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:29,110
You never let me suffer
even the slightest grievance.

152
00:11:29,110 --> 00:11:32,310
You were the one who kept me
from being consumed by hatred—

153
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:36,400
you were the one
who made me look forward to the future.

154
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:39,280
And now you tell me it was all fake?

155
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:42,020
Well, who made your parents
build Lingya Tower?

156
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:43,880
Your parents knew too many secrets—

157
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:45,430
they were always destined to be silenced.

158
00:11:45,430 --> 00:11:46,760
I should even thank you.

159
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:48,600
Without you

160
00:11:49,350 --> 00:11:51,080
bringing me into your home,

161
00:11:51,860 --> 00:11:53,440
I would never have found it.

162
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:59,760
Even your entry into Lingya Tower
to retrieve the antidote—

163
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:01,320
that was all part of my plan.

164
00:12:03,300 --> 00:12:04,310
I originally

165
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:07,200
meant to keep you alive
and slowly torment you to death...

166
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:08,160
but you

167
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:10,650
turned out to be useful.

168
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:12,240
So

169
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:15,970
you were using me all along?

170
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:17,280
Thanks to you,

171
00:12:18,260 --> 00:12:20,570
I was able to expose Kou Wan and Zan Hua,

172
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:23,340
and wipe out

173
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:25,080
all those hidden traitors.

174
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:26,120
Impossible…

175
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,800
you were clearly trapped
by this tower too.

176
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:30,560
You barely escaped

177
00:12:30,560 --> 00:12:31,680
and finally learned
to live like a human again.

178
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:33,550
You clearly despised everything

179
00:12:33,570 --> 00:12:35,120
about this place.

180
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,360
Enough

181
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:39,280
of your little drama.

182
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:40,540
Zhuang Wujiu,

183
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:43,930
the Tower Master
is running out of patience.

184
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:49,120
Father, please spare Yanzhi!

185
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:50,200
You've actually done

186
00:12:50,100 --> 00:12:54,750
♪ Longing lingers between your brows
after our long separation ♪

187
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:51,120
so many treasonous things for her

188
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:53,280
behind my back.

189
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:54,980
If you weren't my daughter,

190
00:12:54,980 --> 00:12:56,920
I would have torn you to pieces.

191
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:58,800
She only entered the tower
to find the antidote—

192
00:12:57,210 --> 00:13:01,050
♪ Words fail, so hear the insects
through the endless night ♪

193
00:12:58,830 --> 00:12:59,800
she meant no harm.

194
00:12:59,800 --> 00:13:00,840
Wujiu,

195
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:02,400
you're far too naive.

196
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:05,270
Do you really not know
Lingya Tower was built by her father?

197
00:13:03,610 --> 00:13:08,770
♪ Obsession melts to ink,
sorrow staining line by line ♪

198
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:07,920
Do you not know
how her parents died?

199
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:10,800
She came into the tower
to avenge her parents.

200
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:15,390
♪ A short letter holds
ten thousand words left unsaid ♪

201
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:12,950
So she must die.

202
00:13:13,880 --> 00:13:15,890
I'll give you one last chance—

203
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:18,240
kill Nan Yanzhi with your own hands.

204
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:21,750
Otherwise, I will show no mercy to anyone

205
00:13:18,350 --> 00:13:23,080
♪ Beneath the lamp,
we watched the days fade into dusk ♪

206
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:24,040
who has ever helped you.

207
00:13:25,210 --> 00:13:28,950
♪ The strings are broken,
and love has vanished like clouds ♪

208
00:13:31,780 --> 00:13:36,910
♪ As splendor fades,
frost seals the heart shut ♪

209
00:13:38,570 --> 00:13:43,810
♪ Flowers bloom and wither, their fading
fragrance leaves silent heartbreak ♪

210
00:13:45,130 --> 00:13:50,810
♪ Half a life of longing—
who understands this devotion ♪

211
00:13:52,150 --> 00:13:57,970
♪ Beneath a lonely lamp, faint light
falls upon the mortal world ♪

212
00:13:59,410 --> 00:14:05,470
♪ The ink still dries, yet these feelings
remain bound to this world ♪

213
00:13:59,680 --> 00:14:00,660
Nan Yanzhi,

214
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:03,670
don't you want revenge
for your parents?

215
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:04,900
Then do it.

216
00:14:05,040 --> 00:14:07,510
This is your last chance.

217
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:12,310
♪ Amid pine winds and bamboo shadows,
I watch the moon sink and stars drift ♪

218
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:09,400
Let me see
whether the skills I taught you

219
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:11,400
are enough for you to kill me.

220
00:14:13,360 --> 00:14:19,110
♪ Through years of blooms and falls,
every word stays buried within ♪

221
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:26,380
♪ All beneath heaven are passing souls—
only my truest heart remains ♪

222
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:33,830
♪ Half a lifetime wandering far and wide,
longing for home ♪

223
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:41,220
♪ Having embraced the boundless stars,
this heart still walks toward the dawn ♪

224
00:14:53,290 --> 00:14:54,900
Your filigree bangle—

225
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:58,220
take it back.

226
00:14:57,070 --> 00:15:01,770
♪ Beneath the lamp,
we watched the days fade into dusk ♪

227
00:15:04,180 --> 00:15:08,050
♪ The strings are broken,
and love has vanished like clouds ♪

228
00:15:10,170 --> 00:15:11,480
Zhuang Wujiu,

229
00:15:10,730 --> 00:15:15,810
♪ As splendor fades,
frost seals the heart shut ♪

230
00:15:11,680 --> 00:15:13,490
from this moment on,

231
00:15:15,110 --> 00:15:17,200
all ties between us are severed.

232
00:15:17,020 --> 00:15:22,480
♪ Flowers bloom and wither, their fading
fragrance leaves silent heartbreak ♪

233
00:15:23,970 --> 00:15:29,700
♪ Half a life of longing—
who understands this devotion ♪

234
00:15:31,140 --> 00:15:36,180
♪ Beneath a lonely lamp, faint light
falls upon the mortal world ♪

235
00:15:38,180 --> 00:15:44,170
♪ The ink still dries, yet these feelings
remain bound to this world ♪

236
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:51,010
♪ Amid pine winds and bamboo shadows,
I watch the moon sink and stars drift ♪

237
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:58,070
♪ Through years of blooms and falls,
every word stays buried within ♪

238
00:15:59,020 --> 00:16:04,850
♪ All beneath heaven are passing souls—
only my truest heart remains ♪

239
00:16:06,470 --> 00:16:12,660
♪ Half a lifetime wandering far and wide,
longing for home ♪

240
00:16:13,650 --> 00:16:17,360
♪ Having embraced the boundless stars,
this heart still journeys toward♪

241
00:16:19,460 --> 00:16:22,530
♪ The dawn ♪

